OL,6,FIn 2015 Siddiqui was 'struck off' the
OL,7,FGeneral Medical Council Register after
OL,8,Fa panel of the Medical Practitioners
OL,9,FTribunal Service found him guilty of
OL,10,Ffailures in performing non-therapeutic
OL,11,Fmale circumcisions in the homes of
OL,12,Ffour babies.
OL,14,FDespite having been 'struck off',
OL,15,FSiddiqui continued to promote and
OL,16,Fprovide a mobile circumcision service,
OL,17,Fcarrying out circumcisions in unsafe,
OL,18,Funsanitary and harmful ways on young
OL,19,Fpatients up to the age of 14 in their
OL,20,Fhomes.
